The Kai 'Oli'Oli is Hawai'i's newest, most state-of-the-art power catamaran in its class! Our exceptional high-speed and long range allow us to take you where no others go.

Our adventure is the only experience that will take you from Ko 'Olina Marina up the entire Waianae Coast to it's northern most tip, the sacred Ka'ena Point.&nbsp;

Learn about the magical history of our Islands and the Waianae coastline (West Coast of Oahu) as our crew enchants you with legends and history of this beautiful land.

If you’re near Hilo on a rainy day, have some indoor fun at Escape Hilo, a thought-heavy, puzzle-oriented mystery experience. “We are the only escape room experience on this side of the island,” says owner Ryan Neal. “We create an experience where the customer can feel fulfilled with their own puzzle-solving abilities. Hilo needs things to do inside when the weather is poor.”

Escape Hilo is perfect for families or groups that don’t want to deal with the physical demands of other activities like laser tag. “What makes escape rooms so fun is that the guests create the experience while solving the puzzles, which is more satisfying than, say, going to a movie or arcade,” adds Neal. “People walk out talking excitedly about the adventure.”

Reservations are recommended, but walk-ins are accepted when there is availability.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Kahuku Golf Course might be the most unique golf experience one can have on Oahu. The nine hole course traces it roots back to sugar mill workers in the 1920s. It's now run by the city of Honolulu. It is a nine hole layout that might be on the most spectacular piece of land of any course on the island.

What makes Kahuku unique is that the course and the amenities are no frills, and that's an understatement. The greens aren't great, the fairways and rough aren't too defined, and beachgoers will wander through the course during your round. But the walk and the scenery are second to none.

Super cheap, no clubhouse, try to bring your own clubs.&nbsp;
